" ... provides a central vehicle for the exchange of basic ideas in heat and mass transfer between research workers and engineers throughout the world. Particular emphasis is focused on original research, both analytical and experimental, and highest priority is given to those contributions which increase the basic understanding of transfer processes and their application to engineering problems. Topics covered include: new methods of measuring and/or correlating transport-property data, energy engineering, and environmental applications of heat and/or mass transfer."
"Academic and industrial researchers, practicing energy engineers specialising in heat transfer and thermodynamic systems, process engineers in chemicals and related sectors."
